File: A crew of a private ambulance service in Port Elizabeth in personal protective equipment (PPE) before checking on a patient affected by COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's death toll has surpassed 16,000 after the Department of Health recorded 126 more COVID-19 deaths. Most of those deaths were in KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng. READ: First human trial of Oxford COVID-19 vaccine shows promise The department recorded over 1,300 new infections, taking the total number of confirmed cases to 663,282. COVID-19 recoveries in SA are at 592,904, translating to a recovery rate of 89.4%. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.